title: Theming\par
description: Using CSS variables and theme tokens.\par
---\par
\par
<Callout>\par
\par
Want to build your theme visually? Use [shadcn/create](/create) to preview colors, radius, fonts, and icons, then generate a preset for your project.\par
\par
</Callout>\par
\par
We use and recommend CSS variables for theming.\par
\par
This gives you semantic theme tokens like `background`, `foreground`, and `primary` that components use by default. Override those tokens in your CSS to change the look of your app without rewriting component classes.\par
\par
```tsx /bg-background/ /text-foreground/\par
<div className="bg-background text-foreground" />\par
```\par
\par
To use CSS variables for theming, set `tailwind.cssVariables` to `true` in your `components.json` file. This is the default.\par
\par
```json \{8\} title="components.json" showLineNumbers\par
\{\par
  "style": "base-nova",\par
  "rsc": true,\par
  "tailwind": \{\par
    "config": "",\par
    "css": "app/globals.css",\par
    "baseColor": "neutral",\par
    "cssVariables": true\par
  \}\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
Tailwind maps these tokens into utilities like `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, and `ring-ring`.\par
\par
Dark mode works by overriding the same tokens inside a `.dark` selector. See the [dark mode docs](/docs/dark-mode/next) for adding a theme provider and toggling the `.dark` class.\par
\par
## Token Convention\par
\par
We use semantic background and foreground pairs. The base token controls the surface color and the `-foreground` token controls the text and icon color that sits on that surface.\par
\par
<Callout className="mt-4">\par
\par
The background suffix is omitted for the surface token. For example, `primary` pairs with `primary-foreground`.\par
\par
</Callout>\par
\par
Given the following CSS variables:\par
\par
```css\par
--primary: oklch(0.205 0 0);\par
--primary-foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0);\par
```\par
\par
The `background` color of the following component will be `var(--primary)` and the `foreground` color will be `var(--primary-foreground)`.\par
\par
```tsx\par
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">Hello</div>\par
```\par
\par
## Theme Tokens\par
\par
These tokens live in your CSS file under `:root` and `.dark`.\par
\par
| Token                                            | What it controls                                       | Used by                                                                      |\par
| ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\par
| `background` / `foreground`                      | The default app background and text color.             | The page shell, page sections, and default text.                             |\par
| `card` / `card-foreground`                       | Elevated surfaces and the content inside them.         | `Card`, dashboard panels, settings panels.                                   |\par
| `popover` / `popover-foreground`                 | Floating surfaces and the content inside them.         | `Popover`, `DropdownMenu`, `ContextMenu`, and other overlays.                |\par
| `primary` / `primary-foreground`                 | High-emphasis actions and brand surfaces.              | Default `Button`, selected states, badges, and active accents.               |\par
| `secondary` / `secondary-foreground`             | Lower-emphasis filled actions and supporting surfaces. | Secondary buttons, secondary badges, and supporting UI.                      |\par
| `muted` / `muted-foreground`                     | Subtle surfaces and lower-emphasis content.            | Descriptions, placeholders, empty states, helper text, and subdued surfaces. |\par
| `accent` / `accent-foreground`                   | Interactive hover, focus, and active surfaces.         | Ghost buttons, menu highlight states, hovered rows, and selected items.      |\par
| `destructive`                                    | Destructive actions and error emphasis.                | Destructive buttons, invalid states, and destructive menu items.             |\par
| `border`                                         | Default borders and separators.                        | Cards, menus, tables, separators, and layout dividers.                       |\par
| `input`                                          | Form control borders and input surface treatment.      | `Input`, `Textarea`, `Select`, and outline-style controls.                   |\par
| `ring`                                           | Focus rings and outlines.                              | Buttons, inputs, checkboxes, menus, and other focusable controls.            |\par
| `chart-1` ... `chart-5`                          | The default chart palette.                             | Charts and chart-driven dashboard blocks.                                    |\par
| `sidebar` / `sidebar-foreground`                 | The base sidebar surface and default sidebar text.     | The `Sidebar` container and its default content.                             |\par
| `sidebar-primary` / `sidebar-primary-foreground` | High-emphasis actions inside the sidebar.              | Active items, icon tiles, badges, and sidebar CTAs.                          |\par
| `sidebar-accent` / `sidebar-accent-foreground`   | Hover and selected states inside the sidebar.          | Sidebar menu hover states, open items, and interactive rows.                 |\par
| `sidebar-border`                                 | Sidebar-specific borders and separators.               | Sidebar headers, groups, and internal dividers.                              |\par
| `sidebar-ring`                                   | Sidebar-specific focus rings.                          | Focused controls inside the sidebar.                                         |\par
| `radius`                                         | The base corner radius scale.                          | Cards, inputs, buttons, popovers, and the derived `radius-*` tokens.         |\par
\par
<Callout className="mt-4">\par
\par
The chart tokens are covered in more detail in the [Chart theming docs](/docs/components/chart#theming).\par
\par
</Callout>\par
\par
## Radius Scale\par
\par
`--radius` is the base radius token for your theme.\par
\par
We derive a small radius scale from it so components can use consistent corner sizes while still sharing a single source of truth.\par
\par
```css title="app/globals.css" showLineNumbers\par
@theme inline \{\par
  --radius-sm: calc(var(--radius) * 0.6);\par
  --radius-md: calc(var(--radius) * 0.8);\par
  --radius-lg: var(--radius);\par
  --radius-xl: calc(var(--radius) * 1.4);\par
  --radius-2xl: calc(var(--radius) * 1.8);\par
  --radius-3xl: calc(var(--radius) * 2.2);\par
  --radius-4xl: calc(var(--radius) * 2.6);\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
This means:\par
\par
- `radius-lg` is the base value.\par
- Smaller radii scale down from `--radius`.\par
- Larger radii scale up from `--radius`.\par
- Changing `--radius` updates the entire radius scale.\par
\par
## Adding New Tokens\par
\par
To add a new token, define it under `:root` and `.dark`, then expose it to Tailwind with `@theme inline`.\par
\par
```css title="app/globals.css" showLineNumbers\par
:root \{\par
  --warning: oklch(0.84 0.16 84);\par
  --warning-foreground: oklch(0.28 0.07 46);\par
\}\par
\par
.dark \{\par
  --warning: oklch(0.41 0.11 46);\par
  --warning-foreground: oklch(0.99 0.02 95);\par
\}\par
\par
@theme inline \{\par
  --color-warning: var(--warning);\par
  --color-warning-foreground: var(--warning-foreground);\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
You can now use `bg-warning` and `text-warning-foreground` in your components.\par
\par
```tsx /bg-warning/ /text-warning-foreground/\par
<div className="bg-warning text-warning-foreground" />\par
```\par
\par
## Base Colors\par
\par
`tailwind.baseColor` controls the default token values generated for your project when you run `init` or use a preset.\par
\par
The available base colors are: **Neutral**, **Stone**, **Zinc**, **Mauve**, **Olive**, **Mist**, and **Taupe**.\par
\par
## Default Theme CSS\par
\par
The following is the full default `neutral` theme scaffold. Copy it into your global CSS file and adjust the tokens as needed.\par
\par
<CodeCollapsibleWrapper>\par
\par
```css showLineNumbers title="app/globals.css"\par
@import "tailwindcss";\par
@import "shadcn/tailwind.css";\par
\par
@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark *));\par
\par
@theme inline \{\par
  --color-background: var(--background);\par
  --color-foreground: var(--foreground);\par
  --color-card: var(--card);\par
  --color-card-foreground: var(--card-foreground);\par
  --color-popover: var(--popover);\par
  --color-popover-foreground: var(--popover-foreground);\par
  --color-primary: var(--primary);\par
  --color-primary-foreground: var(--primary-foreground);\par
  --color-secondary: var(--secondary);\par
  --color-secondary-foreground: var(--secondary-foreground);\par
  --color-muted: var(--muted);\par
  --color-muted-foreground: var(--muted-foreground);\par
  --color-accent: var(--accent);\par
  --color-accent-foreground: var(--accent-foreground);\par
  --color-destructive: var(--destructive);\par
  --color-border: var(--border);\par
  --color-input: var(--input);\par
  --color-ring: var(--ring);\par
  --color-chart-1: var(--chart-1);\par
  --color-chart-2: var(--chart-2);\par
  --color-chart-3: var(--chart-3);\par
  --color-chart-4: var(--chart-4);\par
  --color-chart-5: var(--chart-5);\par
  --color-sidebar: var(--sidebar);\par
  --color-sidebar-foreground: var(--sidebar-foreground);\par
  --color-sidebar-primary: var(--sidebar-primary);\par
  --color-sidebar-primary-foreground: var(--sidebar-primary-foreground);\par
  --color-sidebar-accent: var(--sidebar-accent);\par
  --color-sidebar-accent-foreground: var(--sidebar-accent-foreground);\par
  --color-sidebar-border: var(--sidebar-border);\par
  --color-sidebar-ring: var(--sidebar-ring);\par
  --radius-sm: calc(var(--radius) * 0.6);\par
  --radius-md: calc(var(--radius) * 0.8);\par
  --radius-lg: var(--radius);\par
  --radius-xl: calc(var(--radius) * 1.4);\par
  --radius-2xl: calc(var(--radius) * 1.8);\par
  --radius-3xl: calc(var(--radius) * 2.2);\par
  --radius-4xl: calc(var(--radius) * 2.6);\par
\}\par
\par
