\par
## Without CSS Variables\par
\par
If you do not want to use CSS variables, the CLI can generate components with inline Tailwind color utilities instead.\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest init --no-css-variables\par
```\par
\par
This sets `tailwind.cssVariables` to `false` in your `components.json` file.\par
\par
```tsx /bg-zinc-950/ /text-zinc-50/ /dark:bg-white/ /dark:text-zinc-950/\par
<div className="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-50 dark:bg-white dark:text-zinc-950" />\par
```\par
\par
<Callout className="mt-4">\par
\par
This is an installation-time choice. To switch an existing project, delete and re-install your components.\par
\par
</Callout>\par
}
